      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
      "body" : "It might be a long shot, but is it possible that the exception originates in some 3rd party code?  Maybe it is a (poorly written) exception wrapper, whose toString() simply returns the class name of the wrapped exception, and which fails to provide the underlying stack trace.  Try put something like logger.info(&quot;Exception class = &quot; + exc.class.getCanonicalName()) into your catch block and see what you get."
