      "comment_id" : 14542827,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Thought I&#39;d add the additional bit of information that when the stack trace gets optimized away, it&#39;s because it has gotten fully handled at least once: <a href=\"http://jawspeak.com/2010/05/26/hotspot-caused-exceptions-to-lose-their-stack-traces-in-production-and-the-fix/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">jawspeak.com/2010/05/26/&hellip;</a>"
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 41094,
